headline: Neara Raises More Than $60 Million as Data Centers Pressure Power Grids
summary: Neara, an Australian startup that makes digital models of power networks, has raised more than $60 million to accelerate its expansion as rapid growth in data centers and renewable energy stretch aging electricity grids globally.

headline: Resilient Structures and CenterPoint Energy Announce Strategic Long-Term Supply Agreement to Strengthen Greater Houston Grid
summary: HOUSTON, February 09, 2026--Resilient Structures (RS), a leading manufacturer of high-performance composite utility poles, today announced a long-term supply agreement with CenterPoint Energy (NYSE: CNP), an industry-leading Texas-based electric and natural gas utility serving more than seven million metered customers in six states.
